<h2>A Timelapse Doodle</h2>

<p><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/18832769" width="400" height="295" frameborder="0"></iframe>
</p>

<p>A little doodle inspired by <a href="http://rasterweb.net/raster/tag/tlbot/">Raster's creations with Timelapse Bot</a> and the <a href="http://dhmn.net/Work+Session+18+Dec+2010">12/18/2010 Distributed Hacker Maker Network meeting</a> where I made <a href="http://dhmn.net">an impromptu claymation</a> from stills taken of the meeting.
</p>

<p>While drawing has never really been an interest of mine, drawing in-real-life frames for animation is pretty fun.
</p>

<p>Used in the making:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Canon Powershot A550 (nothing fancy)</li>
<li>Whiteboard/dry erase marker</li>
<li>The free Windows Movie Maker for composition</li>
<li>Fedora 14 Linux and ffmpeg2theora for <a
href="http://archive.org/download/ATimelapseDoodle/atimelapsedoodle-jan-2011.ogv">the Ogg/Theora version of the movie. </a></li>
</ul>
                
